In medical terms, an '''insult''' is the cause of some kind of physical or mental injury. For example, a burn on the skin (the injury) may be the result of a thermal, chemical, radioactive, or electrical event (the insult).<ref>{{Cite book |title=Using Medical Terminology: A Practical Approach |last=Nath |first=Judi L. |authorlink= |last2= |first2= |editorn-last= |editorn-first= |edition= |volume= |year=2006 |origyear= |page=169 |pages= |publisher=Lippincott Williams & Wilkins |place= |url=https://books.google.com/books?id=UEvTZg_5FBIC&lpg=PA345&dq=medical%20term%20insult&pg=PA169#v=onepage&q=%20insult&f=false |accessdate= |isbn=9780781748681 |oclc= }}</ref> Likewise [[sepsis]] and trauma are examples of foreign insults,<ref>{{Cite book |title=Critical Care Nephrology: Expert Consult - Online and Print |last=Ronco, , |first=Claudio |authorlink= |last2=Bellomo |first2=Rinaldo |last3=Kellum |first3=John A. |editorn-last= |editorn-first= |edition= |volume= |year=2008 |origyear= |page=10 |pages= |publisher=Elsevier Health Sciences |place= |url=https://books.google.com/books?id=XkKn96HThzEC&lpg=PA968&dq=medical%20term%20insult&pg=PA10#v=onepage&q=%20insult&f=false |accessdate= |isbn=9781416042525 |oclc= }}</ref> and [[encephalitis]], [[multiple sclerosis]], and brain [[tumor]]s are examples of insults to the brain.<ref>{{Cite book |title=The Medical Basis of Psychiatry |last=Shelton |first= |authorlink= |last2=Hunt |first2= |editor1-last=Fatemi |editor1-first=S. Hossein |editor2-last=Clayton |editor2-first=Paula J. |edition= |chapter=9. Anxiety disorders |volume= |year=2008 |origyear= |page=152 |pages= |publisher=Springer |place= |url=https://books.google.com/books?id=RJOy1vy2RKQC&lpg=PA445&dq=medical%20term%20insult&pg=PA152#v=onepage&q=insult&f=false |accessdate= |isbn=9781597452526 |oclc= }}</ref> Insults may also be categorized as either genetic or environmental.<ref>{{Cite book |title=Langman's Essential Medical Embryology |last=Sadler |first=Thomas W. |authorlink= |last2=Langman |first2=Jan |editorn-last= |editorn-first= |edition= |volume= |year=2005 |origyear= |page=2 |pages= |publisher=Lippincott Williams & Wilkins |place= |url=https://books.google.com/books?id=rinkHXkttaQC&lpg=PA2&dq=medical%20insult&pg=PA2#v=onepage&q=medical%20insult&f=false |accessdate= |isbn=9780781755719 |oclc= }}</ref>
